  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You thrust your arm out, creating an ornate snowflake to catch your enemies off guard.</em> <br />  In a space within 5 feet of you, you create an Ice Construct which gives 1 rank of <em><strong>Chilled</strong></em> and deals 2d6 Cold Damage to creatures that make contact with it. This construct has an AC equal to your Ninjutsu save DC, and 10 HP. Each time a creature makes contact with this Ice Construct, the construct loses 5 HP. You may choose to manifest this construct on a space which a creature occupies.<br />  If you do, the creature must pass a Dexterity saving throw to move 5 feet in any direction to avoid the construct. Upon a failure, the creature is knocked 5 feet back in a direction of your choice, taking 2d6 Cold Damage and gaining 1 rank of <em><strong>Chilled</strong></em>, and becoming <em><strong>Restrained</strong></em> afterwards until their turn next round, or until they take damage, whichever comes first.</p><p>If this jutsu is cast as a <em><strong>Chain 1</strong></em>, the target creature gains 1 additional rank of <em><strong>Chilled</strong></em> on contact with the construct.<br />  If this jutsu is cast as a <em><strong>Chain 2</strong></em>, you gain a +1 bonus to your attack rolls for the next 2 rounds.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by <em>1 <strong>Heat Point</strong></em> and increase the construct's HP by 5 and Cold damage by 2d6.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
